The paper deals with the complexity of evaluating polynomials related to the Ising model, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and mathematical physics. The paper uses techniques from computational complexity theory, graph theory, and algebraic combinatorics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
